56.3	ClickOnce	ClickOnce	ClickOnce is a Microsoft technology that enables the user to install and run a Windows application by clicking a link in a web page. (Such applications are known as Smart clients.) ClickOnce is a component of Microsoft .NET Framework 2.0 and later, supports deploying applications made with Windows Forms or Windows Presentation Foundation. It is similar to Java Web Start for the Java Platform or Zero Install for Linux.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/40/Click1c.PNG/387px-Click1c.PNG
